.TH hsh 1 "April 25 2023" "1.0" "ALX Africa Simple Shell Project"

.SH NAME
hsh - ALX Africa Simple Shell: command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
hsh [options] [command]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a basic command-line interpreter that reads and implements basic commands from user input.

.PP
It is designed to mimic the behavior of the Unix shell, providing users with the ability to execute system commands, manage processes, and perform other common shell functions.

.PP
.B hsh
is built using the C programming language and is compatible with a wide range of Unix-like operating systems.

.SH OPTIONS
The following options are supported:

.SH BUILTINS
.IP help
Call help, display shell help
.IP exit
Exits process and frees memory allocated.
.IP cd
Change directories

.SH EXAMPLES
Below are examples of how to use hsh:

.RS +4
$ hsh
$ ls
README.md shell.c shell.h
$ echo "Hello, world!"
Hello, world!
$ exit
.RE

.SH BUGS
No known bugs until now.

